title: 【雑談】近況はなしゅ【ホロライブ / 星街すいせい】
name: Hoshimachi Suisei

entries.text: Everyone, from the Harajuku Waitini Brand, the idol...
Ah, wait, really? People who can talk...
Wait, does that mean I haven't done a chatting stream since back then?
This is my lesson gear, yep.
I came straight from dance lessons.
And now I'm just chatting like this.
I'm just in my lesson clothes, that's all.
I am Matsukick-in-lesson-clothes right now. Yes.
It's not an emergency broadcast or anything.
I have a song recording tomorrow.
But I have so much I want to talk about.
I feel like I might end up chattering away a bit too much.
Gotta make sure I don't talk *too* much.
If an hour passes, please tell me "An hour passed!"
Surprisingly, in a way... true. Yeah, true.
Hah, you guys finally taking exams?
Yeah, I thought I had a lot of random stuff to talk about.
Going to vote? You guys gotta go vote.
I don't know how you took that, but...
Everyone, actually... a defect was found.
A big issue with the Live...
Even though it was a set, the towel...
They contacted the affected people saying "We'll send it properly, don't worry."
Apparently emails have been sent out.
So if you haven't received one...
Also, there's a high chance it's in your spam folder.
So check your spam folder too.
Did you realize it for the first time from my tweet?
Well, I do that a lot too. When stuff arrives...
I don't rip it open immediately.
That happens, right? So I feel like some people haven't noticed.
But I think I put out a lot of goods last year.
I wonder how much will come out this year.
How much should I put out this year?
Your wallets were seriously in trouble last year, right?
What was I talking about just now?
"Sui-chan, will there be merch sales on the day of the repeat performance?"
I don't really know about this.
I'm asking you guys, is there ever a time when there isn't?
Are there times when there isn't? How is it?
Well, if there is one... If there is, there's no real need to keep quiet about it.
No need to keep quiet, but...
"There wasn't for the First Live?" Eh? Eh, really? You lying? Was that it? I have no memory.
No, how long ago do you think the First was?
Hololive wasn't even listed on the stock exchange yet.
Listed Hololive would do it, right?
One year since that miraculous day.
Sui-chan was like "Wow, really? It was?"
We have about 2 or 3 weeks left this year.
I'm working hard on prep. Dance lessons...
I wanted to strengthen my dancing.
It's not like there are *that* many parts where I sing while dancing.
I wanted to power up the parts where I danced last time.
And said, "Please add tons of steps."
But the steps are too hard, I'm gonna die.
Why did I say that? I'm dying. It's bad.
Why is it so bad? The footwork is crazy.
But I'm going to muscle training once a week. Lessons.
Yeah, that's what I wanted to talk about. The "drag-along" lessons.
"Is Sui-chan making Valentine's chocolates?" Like hell I am.
I'm a person who hates chocolate.
I did it, so I gotta work hard.
"Do you have abs?" I don't have abs yet.
I don't have abs yet, but...
I've been doing these basic lessons since December or November.
I felt like it was time I actually got good at dancing.
So I decided to do basic lessons.
I'm doing them once a week.
Is someone who helps us a lot for Fes and stuff.
"My lessons include stretching and muscle training."
But when I actually tried it, it was insanely tough.
I might have said this before, but...
We do sit-ups at the speed of 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8.
At first, they said "You can just lift your head."
So just lifting my head made my abs hurt like hell.
Seriously, for 3 or 4 days my muscles were screaming.
The muscle pain was that bad.
Now, do I have a six-pack?
I've gotten a bit used to it.
They said just lifting the head was fine.
Even that hurt at first, but I could do it at that speed.
Lifting just my head became pretty easy.
Or inner muscles, I don't know.
It got to the point where lifting just my head didn't hurt that much.
So lately I'm putting more power into my stomach...
And thinking "Maybe I'll lift my shoulders too."
Not just the head, but heaving the shoulders up too.
I'm consciously working hard on the sit-ups.
That's right. So, I'm doing flexibility too.
It is a dance lesson, after all.
Doing flexibility... This also hurts like hell.
You know when you do the splits and go "Hnnngh"?
The teacher says "I'm gonna pull now!" and I go "Yoisho!"
I thought "I want to be flexible even after a bath."
So I try to do the splits just a little bit.
Or do a tiny bit of stretching.
I tried adding that extra effort consciously.
I feel like I'm gaining muscle too.
Noticing the changes in my own body...
But doing this alone is just empty.
Doing it alone is just lonely.
So... There's a text chat for recruiting Holomembers for projects.
It's not a project recruitment, but a private plan.
I ask "Want to do dance lessons together?"
We can have up to 4 people, so 3 others including me.
"It's on me, so does anyone want to do dance lessons?"
The very first time, Suba-chan was there, so I dragged SubaTowa first.
I did it with Suba, Towa, and Nene.
Quite a few EN and ID members came.
Also the ReGLOSS group came a lot.
Ojou came down from the mountains. Yes.
Coming down just for dance lessons.
And they seem to enjoy it, saying they want to go again.
Eh, but Viby is super flexible.
She says "I've been like this since long ago."
She says "I can't go any further than this!"
Yeah, Ao can do full splits.
Su-mon... Well, people who do dance are flexible.
Ririka was on the stiff side.
She's good at dancing but her body is stiff.
I wrote "We will also do muscle training."
People who want to torture themselves...
People who want to torture themselves come.
The masochistic girls are the ones coming so far.
Some people book their own dance lessons.
Some feel they don't need to join mine.
It's pretty fun doing lessons with everyone.
Usually it's just "Let's learn the choreo together" before a Live or Fes.
Aside from that, we don't really have lessons together.
I wanted to do it with everyone happily.
I proposed doing lessons with multiple people.
"If we do individual lessons first and then combine..."
"If someone feels they can't keep up, they might get anxious."
They worried about that, so there were a lot of individual lessons.
Personally, I enjoy doing it with Holomembers.
"That has a point." Yeah, when they say it, it makes sense.
So we often do it individually.
But these dance lessons I host let me do it with everyone.
I forgot to delete the "main stream" tag in the description.
That means I haven't streamed since the Game Festival.
"Club activity vibe." Yeah, it has a club vibe, which is nice.
When someone panics thinking "I can't keep up"...
"It was rough at first but I caught up later." It creates drama.
I think... I've been taking a lot of that.
Well, that adds depth to it.
There's a star on my head.
This one? Ah, this. One more.
So yeah, we're enjoying basic dance lessons together.
So after the basic lesson... We put the Fes dance lesson right after.
Recently... I added the basic lesson...
And some people did like 5 hours of lessons total.
They said "We'll do the lesson together" and came along.
We practiced turns during the basic lesson.
There are numbers for standing positions like 6, 3, 1.
And "put your arms out at chest level."
When doing that, maybe Ririka has a ballet foundation?
Her movement is completely ballet. Like *shanari*.
When preparing, she did it so elegantly.
And Viby has super beautiful turns too.
I think I mentioned it before... On a call-in stream or something.
I told Viby "Your turns are super clean."
When I did the Fes lesson with those two...
She really knows "which angle makes me look cutest."
So I used it as a reference.
There's a lot to learn doing lessons with people.
The teacher is a teacher... So they do the fundamental movements.
But adding "How do I look beautiful?" "Will this look cute?"
"Which angle is better?" "How to make it more like me?"
"Ah, I'll show my color in this part."
You can see that, which is great. Learning.
I'm practicing turns a lot, but... Super bad at them.
Why? Why have I always been bad at turns? I don't get it.
I feel like I wasn't this bad at first.
At some point I developed a complex. I got bad at spinning.
That's why muscle training is necessary.
But for some reason... my stomach is still soft and squishy.
Does once a week not mean anything?
I'm doing quite a bit. It's about time the flab goes away.
It should be like "Oh, I can feel the abs." That would be fine.
"That much intake." Yeah, intake... I am eating.
I don't do diets with food restrictions.
"Ring Fit Ab Set every day." No.
Is once a week too lenient? Gotta do it every day, huh?
If my abs are bad, I gotta do it 8 times a week.
"The stomach is the last to lose weight."
If I restrict food, I won't eat anything anymore.
Huh? I've been eating them lately, trying my best.
And protein drinks definitely taste bad.
I don't want to drink it.
"Can't knock it til you try it."
I shouldn't judge without trying. Gotta drink it once to judge.
"Nee-chan was drinking it for a while."
I eat a ton of meat.
"Sasami (chicken tenders) and stuff." Has to be that type?
There's too many of you drinking it!
How much are you recommending protein?
How many of you have muscles?
There's so many in this stream.
"Chicken breast and sashimi." I eat tons of sashimi.
Does beef tongue make you fat?
I love beef tongue the most.
First I pour salad oil in the pan, *shhh*.
I put that much salad oil.
A sunny-side up fried in salad oil is the tastiest!
I'm not super fat or anything.
My stomach is just a bit squishy.
You know a lot for someone who isn't a member.
Are you someone who quit membership?
It goes back and forth between 46 and 47. Forever.
Even though you aren't a member.
That means core fans exist outside membership too.
It's fine, being a member doesn't make you superior or anything.
That means you watch my streams a lot.
If the meat went everywhere, it'd be fine.
But the meat goes to the stomach first.
I don't do diets that restrict food.
If I skip meals, I die.
If I skip meals or sleep, I die.
"Eat rice at least once a day."
Especially eating rice in the morning gives me energy.
"When Sui-chan declares she's going to eat, we have to let her eat."
"I get the feeling she's about to run out of energy."
"I feel like I have to feed her."
"By the way, what time is morning?"
That's the one thing you shouldn't ask.
Mio, Towa, Ane-machi, and I went on a trip.
Did I say where we went?
Want to go again to *Hauchu Tenbochu.*
We went to Huis Ten Bosch.
I go to Disney a lot.
But I'm like "Just let us drive cars."
Just driving slowly would be fine.
Probably because the roads are narrow.
There are buses inside the park.
I walk 20,000 steps on Disney days.
1.5 times the size of both Tokyo Disney parks combined.
There are like 3 or 4 hotels inside the park itself.
But the hotels are right in the middle of the park.
We were riding the boat, going *vroom*.
There was this beautiful residential area.
I wondered what it was. The boat driver explained stuff.
"On your left is the villa area."
"There are many people actually living here."
Get into Huis Ten Bosch for free.
I want to live there but...
That means that person lives there.
There are rental houses like hotels...
"Can you live there with Bibideba money?"
Not enough to buy a house.
But maybe I should start flipping land soon.
How is it? I don't know how to flip.
Yeah, I should probably do self-defense investment soon.
Wait wait wait... And then it drops, drops, drops.
That seems too likely for me.
We decided to drive to Fukuoka.
I wanted to sit in the passenger seat.
But Towa said "Can I sit in the passenger seat?"
Thought it was fine and sat in the back.
But I'm so glad my legs didn't have to fit there.
If I sit there, I'm like "Just leave it to the navi."
"What is it?" "Eh... Right? Looks like right."
"Better to leave space with the truck."
She got the road wrong once.
Got it wrong once. "This right? That left? Left left? Don't know, left?"
Went left and I think we got off the highway by mistake.
"Ah sorry, wrong. It was straight. Sorry sorry."
"Navi was confusing, sorry. My bad. Sorry, that was my fault."
"I should have checked properly. Sorry sorry sorry."
I was sitting in the back with Nee-chan.
Towa should get a Navi job.
Azukichi too, but she should get one.
1 or 2 hours from Nagasaki to Fukuoka.
I ate them properly. I'm a good girl, right?
I got the one without tomatoes though.
Lettuce and onion I can fudge my way through.
Everyone turns on Navi to hear it...
But you probably actually look at Google Maps.
Bring up Google Maps on phone.
What else was I gonna say?
Can't talk about it in 10 mins.
And now I want to watch Super Kaguya-hime.
My Anime Power is high right now.
"Chi" was too interesting so my Anime Power went up.
Want to watch ZZ (Double Zeta) too.
Wait, want to watch Char's Counterattack too.
Want to watch Origin before that.
I watched all 50 TV episodes properly.
People said "He was a good guy."
It was an ending that gouged out your spirit.
Whether I like the ending or hate it...
Camille faced so many things seriously...
And the result was that. I feel that strongly.
Nothing about it is "good" [for him], but...
Then they said the movies have different content.
It's a trilogy but I only watched the end.
I was shaken by the art style difference.
"Change the helmet?" "If you change the helmet it's fine." He's alive.
It ended super peacefully. It was a Fa lovey-dovey ending.
"How was Char's ending?" Well that happened too, but the very end was happy.
I'd like to see the whole thing with Movie animation though.
"Does the vegetable appear?" I don't know.
Don't say that. Don't say that.
Apparently "If it's not the TV version, it doesn't connect to ZZ."
So I wonder if he appears or is hinted at.
"I don't know the story at all but heard it's interesting."
The title was "About the Movements of the Earth."
The animation was good too. Chi...
I was playing around saying "Dan dan toberu" but I'm truly sorry.
I was playing, but... the OP song and visuals were amazing.
Made me want to rewatch it many times.
And finishing in 25 episodes was clean.
You might not know what I'm saying, but...
Chi doesn't feel like it ended at all.
Well, the core of the story continues.
I looked up people like that on Wikipedia.
Learned they studied philosophy at university.
So I watched with Business Friend (Miko).
She seems to be watching it.
After watching, works that expand your view are amazing.
"In this 15th century, there were villains and heroes..."
"But everyone was a key player in creating one history."
"So there are no enemies or allies."
It was a really good story.
The lack of plot armor hit me.
I have a weakness for non-convenient plots.
Since I liked the Zeta Gundam ending, you probably know.
But I understand the feeling of "it can't be helped."
Or maybe because they're a philosopher...
They throw something at the audience.
"So which is it, what does it mean?"
But it was a good story.
Or people about to give up.
Put a lot of effort in.
"Writer of this and this past Precure."
Apparently they are writing Wonderful Precure.
I like the Precure seasons they wrote before.
So I'm looking forward to the ending.
"Is Precure a detective this time?" Yes.
Not much in the past though.
But this time it's strictly hidden.
Hard ones were Cure Muse, Cure Passion...
Those were fun like "Who is it?!"
Thinking about it, this "Who is it" feeling is nostalgic.
Eh, it's this one right? Gotchard.
Thinking of catchy phrases is amazing.
If a woman enters there, I'll get scolded.
But catchy phrases make you want to say them.
Kids definitely say it at elementary school.
Thinking of words you want to say is genius.
"There are female voices too." Ah, there are?
I'm singing the opening tie-up. Please watch it.
Mayonaka Heart Tune... inherits the flow of Nisekoi or Quintuplets.
"Who was the girl I was close with long ago?"
But if I had to say...
Anime I want to watch: Super Kaguya-hime.
Even on TV the art was super high effort.
In one movie... TV anime has deadlines rushing you.
You can see that intention clearly.
Also looking forward to World Trigger Reboot.
Jump is putting effort in. Animation.
World Trigger... If they put effort in again...
It has the potential to be a national anime.
Shueisha probably thinks "Let's make it a national anime."
By the way, I didn't copy this.
"What happens if we redraw that work now?"
The old cel animation was good, but...
I want to see that too.
Also hurry up with Sakura-chan sequel.
Excuse me. Would you please do it?
Won't you do Sakura-chan Clear Card Arc?
It would be weird if it wasn't.
That was Hoshimachi Suisei's chat stream.
I thought about it a lot.
